<subSubSection pageNumber="597" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="597">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="597">Note:</emphasis>
This has a very confused synonymy. Lewis argued that 
<taxonomicName authority="Ker" authorityName="Ker" class="Liliopsida" family="Iridaceae" genus="Babiana" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="plicata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="597">Babiana plicata</emphasis>
Ker
</taxonomicName>
is not based on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1756" class="Liliopsida" family="Iridaceae" genus="Ixia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="plicata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="597">I. plicata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, so 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Linnaeusâ€™">Linnaeus'</normalizedToken>
name is not available for use in the genus despite its priority. She was also aware that the Sparrman collection on the right of sheet 59.6 (LINN) was a later addition to the herbarium and therefore restricted her type choice to the specimen to the left.
</paragraph>
